Adjust rack to top position and heat broiler to high or oven to 500 degrees.

Wash and dry all produce. In a #small pot{}, combine @Jasmine Rice{1/2%cup}, 3/4 cup water, and a pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve, peel, and thinly slice @Yellow Onion{1}. Core, deseed, and dice @Long Green Pepper{1}. Dice @Roma Tomato{1}. Zest and quarter @Lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, lime juice to taste, and a pinch of @salt{}. Add water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. In a separate small bowl, combine tomato, a drizzle of @Olive Oil{1%teaspoon}, a pinch of @salt{}, and lime juice and zest to taste.

Heat a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add @Italian Chicken Sausage Mix{9%ounce} and cook, breaking up meat into pieces, ~{1-2%minutes}. Add onion, green pepper, and @Southwest Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}. Cook, stirring, until veggies are lightly browned and sausage is cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add cooked rice, @Chicken Stock Concentrate{1}, @Butter{1%tablespoon}, and 1/4 cup water to pan. Stir to thoroughly combine.

> TIP: If pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture now to a #baking dish{}.

Top sausage mixture with @Pepper Jack Cheese{1/2%cup}. Broil or bake until cheese is bubbly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Top broiled sausage mixture with salsa and crema. Drizzle with @Hot Sauce{1%teaspoon} if desired. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.